The paper discusses the use of semantics in zero-shot learning, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper proposes a new convolutional neural network (CNN) framework, which involves the use of semantic constraints for recognition, indicating that it may also fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of semantic correlations, which is a topic related to natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on several datasets, indicating that it may also fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
